<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[828,1437,389,604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,982,389,412]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Distribution.</emphasis>
Most of North Europe, in Central and Southern Europe known from the biggest mountain ranges: Alps, Pyrenees, and Carpathians (
<bibRefCitation author="SCHEUCHL" box="[1178,1340,453,476]" firstAuthor="SCHEUCHL" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" refId="ref8815" refString="SCHEUCHL E. 2000: Illustrierte Bestimmungstabellen der Wildbienen Deutschlands und Osterreichs. Band I: Anthophoridae. - 2. erweiterte Auflage. Erwin Scheuchl, Velden, 158 pp." type="book" year="2000">SCHEUCHL 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="AMIET" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="AMIET" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" refId="ref8315" refString="AMIET F., HERRMANN M., MULLER A. &amp; NEUMEYER R. 2007: Apidae 5. Ammobates, Ammobatoides, Anthophora, Biastes, Ceratina, Dasypoda, Epeoloides, Epeolus, Eucera, Macropis, Melecta, Melitta," type="book" year="2007">AMIET et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). This species is probably not endemic to Europe but likely occurs also in Siberia (
<bibRefCitation author="BISCHOFF" box="[1179,1339,517,540]" firstAuthor="BISCHOFF" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref8389" refString="BISCHOFF H. 1930: Beitrag zur Kenntnis palaarktischer Arten der Gattung Epeolus. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 1930: 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1930">BISCHOFF 1930</bibRefCitation>
). Several records are known also from North Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="BOGUSCH P. &amp; HADRAVA J." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" refId="ref8412" refString="BOGUSCH P. &amp; HADRAVA J. in press: The bees of the genera Epeolus Latreille, 1802 and Triepeolus Robertson, 1901 (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae: Epeolini) of Europe: taxonomy, identification key, distribution, and ecology. Zootaxa." title="The bees of the genera Epeolus Latreille, 1802 and Triepeolus Robertson, 1901 (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae: Epeolini) of Europe: taxonomy, identification key, distribution, and ecology" type="book chapter" year="in">BOGUSCH &amp; HADRAVA, in press</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1040,1306,581,604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
New record for 
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1301,581,604]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
